definition: to squeeze through/to force one's way through
to crowd in/to cram in/to force others aside/to press/to squeeze/to find (time in one's busy schedule)
to cross/to go over/to pass (time)/to celebrate (a holiday)/to live/to get along/excessively/too-

sentences.english: She crushed the bootee back into the basket and squeezed past the guardhouse.
sentences.chinese: 她把幼兒小毛線鞋放進籃子裏面，擠過警衛室。

sentences.english: She muscled through the throngs of people, frantically searching for David.
sentences.chinese: 她使勁擠過人羣，拼命尋找戴維。

sentences.english: Robinovitz pushed past the queue jamming the passageway outside the infirmary .
sentences.chinese: 羅賓諾維茨擠過在醫務室門外阻塞了通道的長隊。

sentences.english: They crowded through the gate into the stadium.
sentences.chinese: 他們擠過大門，進入運動場。

sentences.english: He corkscrewed his way through the crowd.
I squeeze carefully through the crowd.
sentences.chinese: 我小心翼翼地擠過這羣人。

sentences.english: We wormed our way through the crowd .
They crowded through the gates into the stadium.
sentences.chinese: 他們擠過大門，湧入運動場。

sentences.english: I poked through a bazaar crammed with good.
sentences.chinese: 我擠過了堆滿貨物的集市。

sentences.english: He bulled his way throught the crowd into the room.
The car corkscrewed through the traffic jam.
sentences.chinese: 那部車子蜿蜒擠過交通阻塞的道路。

sentences.english: In the Amazonian jungle he could not squeeze it between the trees.
sentences.chinese: 在亞馬遜叢林，他不能把車子擠過樹叢。

sentences.english: He brawled his way through the crowd.
He hustled around the dining room serving a combination of eggs and attitude.
sentences.chinese: 他擠過餐廳用很好的服務態度上了一份雞蛋。
